<dl id="n53060k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53060k">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53060k"> 60(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Esk. liv &amp; dead</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[When we realise that most languages do not distinguish gender, that, for instance, the <mark>Eskimos</mark> segregate things into <mark>living and dead</mark> objects, we would perforce admire the linguistic imagination of the Eskimos and consider our own sex-driven phantasy merely barbarian.]</font> <small> Fritz Mauthner, <a name="FMBK1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#FMBK1"><cite title="source">Beitr&auml;ge zu einer Kritik der Sprache.</cite></a> 3 vols (1901-2) III 28</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
